  "body": "kind feature\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nCurrently there is no mechanism to report metrics as the flex plugins are not enabled to collect metrics. All flex volumes lack this feature as compared to in-tree/built-in drivers even though it is possible to collect such metrics for most of the plugins.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nDepending on the availability of the metrics from the mounted FS, flex plugins should allow to report metrics for the FS.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nThe default behavior that can be proved easily by just running a command similar to the following command on a node that is running a flex volume. This will show that there are no metrics collected for flex volumes.\r\nkubectl proxy  \r\n$curl 127.0.0.1:8001/api/v1/nodes/<IP>/proxy/stats/summary**\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.12\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: local x86\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Ubuntu 16.04\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): Linux KubeStorage 4.4.0-130-generic #156-Ubuntu SMP Thu Jun 14 08:53:28 UTC 2018 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n- Install tools: \r\n- Others:\r\n/sig storage",
